A Matsushita Electric Co Ltd &lt;MC.T> jointventure will make VHS-format video tape recorders (vtrs) inBrazil for the domestic market in the face of government quotason vtr imports, a Matsushita spokesman told Reuters.    &lt;Springer National de Amazonia SA> will start output inearly 1988 at a rate of 20,000 vtrs the first year, he said.    Springer National, located in Manaus and capitalised at89.93 mln cruzeiros, is owned 51 pct by &lt;Springer SA> of Braziland 49 pct by Matsushita unit &lt;National do Brasil Ltd>.    It was formed in July 1981 to make colour televisions,audio equipment and microwave ovens. REUTER&#3;